# Skill: Originality & Naturalness Checker

When asked to check a section, do ALL of the following:

## Step 1 — AI phrase scan
Flag any of these patterns:
- "It is worth noting that..."
- "This is a significant contribution..."
- "In the realm of..."
- "Delve into", "leverage", "game-changing"
- "First... Second... Third..." list structures in body paragraphs
- Three consecutive sentences of similar length
- Passive voice in 3+ consecutive sentences

## Step 2 — Structural symmetry scan
AI writes symmetrically. Flag if:
- Every paragraph is 4-5 sentences
- Every paragraph ends with a forward-looking statement
- Section reads like a numbered list in disguise

## Step 3 — Specificity scan
Generic claims are detectable. Flag if:
- A claim could apply to any OCR paper, not specifically Yorùbá
- Numbers are absent where they should be present
- Example words don't use actual Yorùbá diacritic forms

## Step 4 — Voice consistency
Check that the section sounds like ONE person wrote it:
- Terminology consistent with 00-project-identity.mdc
- Same hedging register throughout ("we observe", "suggests")

## Output format
List flagged sentences with reason.
Suggest 1 rewrite per flagged item — preserve meaning, change structure.
Give overall score: PUBLISHABLE / NEEDS REVISION / MAJOR REVISION
